                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.51/1132: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-08T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 8, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your telegram No. 19, March 5. My telegram No. 33, March 7.<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d412fn22">Not printed.</note> Informed at Ministry of Foreign
                    Affairs that in spite of British pressure commitment will be lived up to.
                    Coupons sterling issue due April 15 will be paid in full but as regards other
                    coupons Polish proposal to British [is] identic with proposal made American
                    bondholders. Confirmed this information Ministry of Finance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
